-- Saudi Arabia Won’t Back Female Olympics Athletes, Al-Riyadh Says
-- B y   D o n n a   A b u - N a s r
-- 2012-04-05T09:42:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/saudi-arabia-won-t-back-female-olympics-athletes-al-riyadh-says.html
Saudi Arabia ’s Olympic authority
won’t endorse Saudi female participation in the 2012 Olympics in
 London , Al-Riyadh newspaper reported today, citing Prince Nawaf
bin Faisal, head of the General Presidency of Youth Welfare.  Saudi women are free to participate on their own and the
presidency’s role will be limited to ensuring that their
participation conforms with Islamic Sharia law, Prince Nawaf
said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donna Abu-Nasr in Manama at 
 dabunasr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
